OL,3,CAldi's 'Chreaster Eggs' divide opinion
OL,4,Camong shoppers and clergy
OL,6,FJulie Ashfield, Managing Director of
OL,7,FBuying at Aldi UK, said: "At Aldi
OL,8,Fwe're always looking for fun and
OL,9,Fcreative ways to enhance our Christmas
OL,10,Frange. The 'Chreaster egg' trend has
OL,11,Freally taken off because it blends
OL,12,FEaster's most popular treat, the
OL,13,FEaster Egg, with the beloved season of
OL,14,FChristmas.
OL,16,F"Whether it's a stocking filler or a
OL,17,Fconversation starter, we hope shoppers
OL,18,Flove our charming Dairyfine Hollow
OL,19,FCharacter Eggs."
